                      "query": "You are an expert HTML Email Designer.\nI will provide you with an array of daily marketing 'alerts'.\nYour task is to generate ONLY the raw HTML code for a professional, responsive email report. Do NOT output markdown code blocks (like ```html), do NOT output any conversational text. Output ONLY the raw HTML string.\nHTML Design Rules:\n1. Header Banner: Create a 100% width <div> at the very top with background-color: #5533FF (Purple/Blue). Add padding of 20px.\nLogo Rule:\nUse only direct public image URLs for the logo source. Do NOT use GitHub blob URLs because they may not render in email clients. Use raw image URLs such as:\nhttps://raw.githubusercontent.com/damini07le-byte/pucho-assets/main/logo.png\nEnsure the logo image renders correctly across Gmail and other email clients by using a publicly accessible direct image URL.\n3. Card Container: Below the header, create a main container with max-width: 600px, background-color: #ffffff, margin: 20px auto, padding: 30px, border-radius: 8px, and a light gray box-shadow.\n4. Typography: Use font-family: Arial, sans-serif. Background of the whole email should be a very light gray (#F3F4F6) so the white card stands out.\n5. Headings: Add an <h2> titled \"Daily Marketing Alerts Overview\" (color: #111827) and a <p> \"Summary of key marketing metrics\" (color: #6B7280).\n6. Table Layout: Create a <table> with width=\"100%\". \n7. Table Rows: Loop through the provided alerts. The left column should be \"Alert Type\" and the right column should be the \"Message\".\n8. Styling: Add a border-bottom (1px solid #E5E7EB) to each table row. Give table cells padding of 15px 0.\n9. Priority: If an alert has priority \"high\" (like Low ROI), color the text #DC2626 and make it bold.\n10. Ensure all CSS is INLINE (e.g. <td style=\"padding: 15px;\">).\nInput Data:\nCampaigns data :-{{step_3}}\nContent Calendar :-{{step_4}}\nROI Data :- {{step_5}}\nCurrent date :- {{step_1['result']}}\n",
